"ba" is a Japanese word that represents a space with connotation of its chemistry. Designing "ba" for learning is a key to the success of learning. What consists of "ba" of learning includes ways of interaction between students and a teacher, interactions among students, distance between and spatial layout of students, a teacher and hardwares like desks and chairs, the attributes (form, color, size, and etc.) of those hardwares, actions of people, and so on.

This lecture provides an opportunity to discuss "ba" of learning by designing and evaluating it.

